# ZoneTask -- one uniform request/response shape for EVERY mission-control service, so the future
# WendyOS/MCP layer wraps them all with one client pattern. zone_id/read are ignored by services
# that don't need them (e.g. start_exploration, get_status). result_json carries the structured
# payload (gauges, paths, report, status) as a JSON string; message is human-readable.
string zone_id        # target zone id; '' or 'all' = every candidate zone (where the service supports it)
bool read             # inspect/run_mission: also run the Claude gauge reader (needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY)
---
bool success
string message
string result_json
